data-triple-N3.o: "The Louvin Brothers were an American country music duo comprised of brothers Ira Lonnie Loudermilk (1924–1965) and Charlie Elzer Loudermilk (1927–2011) — known as Ira and Charlie Louvin, respectively. The Brothers helped popularize close harmony, a genre of country music and are cousins to John D. Loudermilk, a Nashville Songwriters Hall of Fame member."@en
